output.analysis:
Let's analyze this post according to our criteria:
1. Has CMF: No CMF number is present, but this isn't determinative.
2. Refers to candidate: Yes, explicitly refers to George Simion, who is a presidential candidate (Position #2 on the ballot).
3. Addresses wide population: Yes, this is a paid advertisement reaching 5,000-6,000 impressions, promoting a public march.
4. Electoral objective: Yes, the post promotes a march supporting George Simion with hashtags like #georgesimionpresedinte and #alegeri2024, clearly indicating electoral intent.
5. Journalism: No, this is not journalistic content but rather an announcement for a political rally.
6. Personal opinion: No, this is an organized campaign event announcement.
Key factors: - The post promotes a march specifically supporting a presidential candidate - Uses campaign-specific hashtags (#georgesimionpresedinte) - Is being promoted after the end of the legal campaign period - Has significant reach through paid promotion - Explicitly electoral in nature

conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis: This post clearly constitutes electoral propaganda because: - It explicitly promotes a presidential candidate - Uses campaign-specific messaging and hashtags - Is a paid advertisement reaching thousands - Organizes a march specifically to support a presidential candidate - Takes place after the campaign period has ended
conclusion.message-for-police: SC VIDEO DANCRYS-STUDIO SRL, pentru incalcarea articolului 55 t) din Legea 370/2004, prin promovarea unui mars de sustinere pentru candidatul la presedintie George Simion dupa incheierea perioadei de campanie electorala. Postarea cu ID-ul 1146734783545268, publicata dupa ora 18:00 pe 23.11.2024, promoveaza explicit un eveniment de sustinere electorala, folosind hashtag-uri precum #georgesimionpresedinte si #alegeri2024, si mobilizeaza cetatenii la un mars de sustinere pentru candidat, reprezentand o forma clara de propaganda electorala in afara perioadei legale de campanie. Postarea a fost promovata ca reclama platita pe Facebook si Instagram, atingand intre 5000 si 6000 de afisari, demonstrand intentia clara de a influenta comportamentul electoral al cetatenilor in perioada in care acest lucru este interzis prin lege.
